13:44.254 --> 13:45.487
No problem.

13:45.555 --> 13:47.456
In high school,
I was kind of a band geek.

13:47.524 --> 13:49.691
It's nice to come back
as a cool bartender.

13:51.461 --> 13:54.894
As a moderately cool
bartender.

13:56.263 --> 13:57.896
It's nice to come back
as a bartender?

13:57.964 --> 13:58.997
[ laughs ]

14:02.767 --> 14:04.268
[ knock on door ]

14:04.336 --> 14:06.503
Can you guys kick in
for the pizza for once?

14:06.571 --> 14:08.104
I am unemployed,
you know.

14:15.646 --> 14:18.515
Hey, I'm kylie.

14:18.582 --> 14:21.317
Which one of you little maniacs
is marvin mcfadden?

14:21.385 --> 14:22.785
* oh, yeah *

14:22.853 --> 14:23.919
Uh, that's me.

14:23.987 --> 14:26.154
I'm here for our date.

14:26.222 --> 14:28.556
I think
there's been a mistake.

14:28.624 --> 14:31.661
Your profile said that
you're tall and thin,

14:31.729 --> 14:33.962
With a good body
and really big...

14:35.531 --> 14:37.031
...Hands.

14:39.534 --> 14:40.668
Oh, my.

14:40.736 --> 14:42.870
I hear there's a dance
at the school.

14:42.938 --> 14:44.238
Do you want to go?

14:44.306 --> 14:45.239
No.

14:46.474 --> 14:48.708
Well, I mean, yes,
but [clears throat]

14:48.776 --> 14:49.910
It's just that...

14:49.977 --> 14:52.679
Why are <i>youon a dating ?</i>

14:52.747 --> 14:54.881
You could get a date
with anyone on the planet.

14:54.949 --> 14:57.583
You're not, like,
a dude, are you?

15:00.186 --> 15:02.120
[ clears throat ]

15:03.523 --> 15:05.424
Satisfied?

15:05.493 --> 15:07.427
Yeah.
Yeah.                   Yeah.

15:07.495 --> 15:11.898
[ yello's "oh, yeah" plays ]

15:11.966 --> 15:16.301
* such a good child,
a really good child *

15:34.210 --> 15:36.078
* beautiful, beautiful *

15:38.547 --> 15:42.014
* oh, yeah *

15:42.082 --> 15:46.017
* oh, yeah, yeah, yeah *

15:54.958 --> 15:56.225
Ugh!

15:56.293 --> 15:57.994
[ box clatters ]

15:59.563 --> 16:03.465
* such a good child,
a really good child *

16:06.635 --> 16:09.270
Oh, no.
It's mom's birthday.

16:09.338 --> 16:13.774
[ "if you were here" plays ]

16:13.842 --> 16:15.909
[ sighs ]

16:32.824 --> 16:35.058
I just want to say
how grateful I am

16:35.126 --> 16:39.328
That you're all
taking this ride with me.

16:39.396 --> 16:41.997
Now let's go make
someone's favorite movie!

16:42.065 --> 16:45.267
* if you were here,
I could deceive you *

16:45.334 --> 16:48.569
It sounded better in my head.

16:48.637 --> 16:49.970
Don't worry.

16:50.038 --> 16:52.206
I'll start the slow clap for you
if no one else does.

16:52.273 --> 16:54.340
What are you
still doing here?

16:54.408 --> 16:56.876
Well, it just occurred to me
that you spent the entire day

16:56.943 --> 16:59.211
Making everyone else
feel ready for tomorrow.

16:59.279 --> 17:00.645
How do <i>you</i> feel?

17:02.348 --> 17:03.614
Nervous.

17:03.682 --> 17:05.782
I...I've been around movie sets
my whole life,

17:05.851 --> 17:08.018
But I've never been
in the director's chair.

17:08.086 --> 17:10.787
I was pretty nervous, to
for my first big part.

17:10.855 --> 17:12.655
But I just
kept asking myself,

17:12.723 --> 17:14.489
"how would
julia roberts do it?"

17:14.557 --> 17:16.324
[ chuckles ]

17:16.392 --> 17:18.025
She's my favorite actress.

17:18.093 --> 17:20.027
So who's your favorite
director?

17:20.095 --> 17:22.896
John hughes.

17:22.964 --> 17:25.632
You know, "ferris bueller,"

17:25.699 --> 17:27.866
"breakfast club,"
"sixteen candles."

17:27.934 --> 17:30.935
Those weren't just movies
about teenagers.

17:31.003 --> 17:35.172
They were about the struggle
everyone has to find themselves.

17:35.239 --> 17:37.473
Talk about a director
with a clear vision.

17:37.541 --> 17:40.075
I-I'd like to make a movie
half as good as his.

17:40.142 --> 17:42.476
Then why don't you take a cue
from john hughes?

17:42.544 --> 17:43.778
Clear your vision.

17:43.845 --> 17:45.946
Take the night off
and come to the school.

17:46.014 --> 17:47.480
Maybe even
dance with brooke.

17:47.548 --> 17:48.814
[ chuckles ]

17:48.882 --> 17:50.582
I don't know, alex.

17:50.650 --> 17:52.317
Um...

17:52.385 --> 17:54.787
I have to find an outfit
from the '80s.

17:54.855 --> 17:57.791
Actually,
I've got that covered.

17:57.858 --> 17:59.659
I thought you might
change your mind.

17:59.726 --> 18:02.962
But just so we're clear --
this is not a date.

18:03.029 --> 18:05.864
It's not even
date-ish.

18:10.703 --> 18:12.203
Not bad.

18:17.440 --> 18:24.010
* and if you were here,
I could deceive you *

18:26.612 --> 18:31.081
* and if you were here,
I could deceive you *

18:31.149 --> 18:34.483
Brooke davis --
stunning in any decade.

18:36.819 --> 18:43.556
* and if you were here,
you would believe *

18:52.850 --> 18:54.184
Hi, everyone!

18:54.252 --> 18:57.687
Thank you so much for coming out
and supporting the arts!

18:57.755 --> 18:59.455
[ cheers and applause ]

18:59.523 --> 19:01.757
So, please, everyone,
give what you can

19:01.825 --> 19:05.893
And have a gnarly,
totally tubular time!

19:05.961 --> 19:08.395
Um...Oh.

19:08.463 --> 19:09.897
Where's the beef?

19:11.333 --> 19:14.333
Oh. Okay, um,
ladies and gentlemen,

19:14.401 --> 19:15.901
Please welcome...

19:15.969 --> 19:16.968
Cheap trick!        Cheap trick!

19:17.036 --> 19:18.837
[ cheers and applause ]

19:18.905 --> 19:21.373
[ intro to "I want you
to want me" plays ]

19:30.449 --> 19:35.087
* I want you to want me *

19:35.154 --> 19:39.825
* I need you to need me *

19:39.893 --> 19:43.762
* I'd love you to love me *

19:43.829 --> 19:48.632
* I'm begging you to beg me *

19:48.700 --> 19:51.465
You notice how kylie
smelled like strawberries?

19:51.533 --> 19:53.062
Yeah.

19:54.695 --> 19:56.328
Mouth totally owes us.

19:56.396 --> 19:58.062
[ cellphone rings ]

19:58.130 --> 19:59.764
Ooh.

19:59.831 --> 20:03.001
It's a text from haley.

20:03.069 --> 20:04.803
"how's it going
with jamie?"

20:04.871 --> 20:05.737
[ scoffs ]

20:07.406 --> 20:08.973
* I get home early from work *

20:09.041 --> 20:14.145
* if you say that you love me *

20:14.212 --> 20:18.315
* didn't I, didn't I,
didn't I see you crying? *

20:18.383 --> 20:23.153
* oh, didn't I, didn't I,
didn't I see you crying? *

20:23.220 --> 20:26.823
* feeling all alone without
a friend, you feel like dying *

20:26.891 --> 20:29.859
Alexander coyne,
this is haley james scott.

20:29.927 --> 20:31.895
Hey. I'm a big fan.
Oh, thanks.

20:31.962 --> 20:34.497
I am -- I am, too, of your
detective work with tubbs.

20:34.564 --> 20:36.031
[ laughs ]

20:36.099 --> 20:38.034
You know, this is a big night
for haley.

20:39.835 --> 20:41.770
When we were
in high school,

20:41.838 --> 20:44.439
She was always trying
to bring back the '80s fashion.

20:44.506 --> 20:45.873
You got your wish!

20:45.941 --> 20:48.376
Oh, I did! I did.

20:48.443 --> 20:50.011
Um, excuse me.

20:50.078 --> 20:51.679
'kay.

20:51.746 --> 20:56.083
Grubbs,
make me something...Strong.

20:56.151 --> 20:57.317
[ sighs ]

20:59.554 --> 21:01.922
What?
You need to see my I.D.?

21:01.989 --> 21:03.523
Grubbs, you flatter me.

21:03.591 --> 21:05.691
* I want you to want me *

21:05.759 --> 21:07.226
Wow.

21:07.294 --> 21:08.894
I had no idea.

21:08.962 --> 21:11.931
You're 5'4".

21:11.999 --> 21:13.365
Thank you.

21:13.433 --> 21:16.200
[ chuckles ]

21:16.268 --> 21:17.634
[ sighs ]

21:17.702 --> 21:19.902
Good talk, grubbs.

21:19.970 --> 21:21.103
[ sighs ]

21:25.607 --> 21:27.773
[ cheers and applause ]

21:27.841 --> 21:30.409
[ wind whipping ]

21:45.824 --> 21:48.358
[ doors rattle ]

21:59.602 --> 22:00.969
[ intro to cheap trick's
"surrender" plays ]

22:07.010 --> 22:08.677
I swear, I'm gonna
kill that kid.

22:08.745 --> 22:09.979
Come on.

22:12.615 --> 22:16.018
* mother told me,
yes, she told me *

22:16.086 --> 22:19.460
* I'd meet girls like you *

22:19.527 --> 22:22.863
* she also told me, "stay away *

22:22.931 --> 22:26.599
* you'll never know
what you'll catch" *

22:26.667 --> 22:33.237
* but just the other day,
I heard a soldier falling off *

22:33.304 --> 22:35.872
* some indonesian junk... *

22:35.939 --> 22:38.774
So, your profile said
you like to dance.

22:38.842 --> 22:41.143
Maybe after
a few more drinks.

22:41.210 --> 22:44.145
* mommy's all right,
daddy's all right *

22:44.212 --> 22:47.448
I'll be right back.

22:47.515 --> 22:48.849
* surrender *

22:48.916 --> 22:50.517
What her profile
<i>should</i> have said

22:50.584 --> 22:51.950
Is "like millie on steroids."

22:52.018 --> 22:54.619
* but don't give yourself away *

22:54.686 --> 22:56.387
* ay-ay-ay *

22:56.455 --> 23:00.157
* aaay, aay-aaay *

23:00.224 --> 23:01.792
It took me four hours

23:01.859 --> 23:04.928
To get the smoothie
out of my hair, bitch.

23:04.996 --> 23:06.629
Yes, well, I'm the one
who has to drive home

23:06.697 --> 23:08.330
In a car with "slut"
written all over it.

23:08.398 --> 23:10.665
I was just trying
to increase your chances

23:10.733 --> 23:11.967
Of getting rear-ended.

23:12.035 --> 23:13.835
Look, I'm sorry, okay?

23:13.903 --> 23:15.203
I shouldn't have
poured smoothie on you.

23:15.271 --> 23:16.204
I apologize.

23:17.606 --> 23:19.272
Truce?

23:19.340 --> 23:23.442
How american of you to pick
a fight that you can't win.

23:23.510 --> 23:24.743
And just so you know,

23:24.811 --> 23:27.145
Clay told me
that he didn't believe in love.

23:27.213 --> 23:29.480
So good luck with that.

23:29.548 --> 23:34.750
* I've known her
all these years *

23:34.817 --> 23:38.018
* mommy's all right,
daddy's all right *

23:38.086 --> 23:41.421
* they just seem
a little weird *

23:41.489 --> 23:44.858
* surrender, surrender *

23:44.925 --> 23:47.760
* but don't give yourself away *

23:47.828 --> 23:49.795
The highway's this way.
I think.

23:49.862 --> 23:51.463
Clay: You look on
the bright side, nate --

23:51.531 --> 23:53.335
I mean, if we actually
live through this thing,

23:53.403 --> 23:54.905
Think
of the endorsement deals.

23:54.972 --> 23:56.239
I mean,
on gps units alone.

23:56.307 --> 23:57.941
Like, "I never
would've gotten lost

23:58.009 --> 23:59.442
If it had only
been for my --"

23:59.510 --> 24:00.910
Shut up!
<i>Please</i> shut up!

24:00.978 --> 24:02.211
Trying to make
conversation.

24:02.279 --> 24:03.779
That's the thing --
you're talking.

24:03.847 --> 24:04.913
You're <i>always</i> talking,
man.

24:04.981 --> 24:06.214
Oh, I'm so sorry.

24:06.282 --> 24:07.682
I didn't realize
that the human compass

24:07.750 --> 24:10.718
Needed complete silence
to concentrate.

24:12.120 --> 24:14.787
You know, maybe we should have
stayed with the pigs.

24:14.855 --> 24:18.023
'cause it seems to me
that you've gotten us lost.

24:18.091 --> 24:20.558
Me?

24:20.626 --> 24:22.326
We wouldn't even
be here right now

24:22.394 --> 24:24.227
If you hadn't insisted
on driving to atlanta

24:24.295 --> 24:25.628
For a guys' road trip.

24:25.696 --> 24:27.496
If you hadn't have missed
tree hill in the rain,

24:27.564 --> 24:29.431
If you hadn't have driven over
those tire spikes,

24:29.499 --> 24:31.999
I would be home
right now, clay!

24:32.067 --> 24:34.101
I'm on the road
for half the year!

24:34.169 --> 24:37.070
The <i>least</i> I can do is be home
for my wife's birthday.

24:37.138 --> 24:39.839
Nate, I know haley.
She'll understand.

24:39.907 --> 24:41.241
Well,
she shouldn't have to.

24:41.309 --> 24:43.109
You'd know that
if you were ever married.

24:43.177 --> 24:45.577
[ sighs ]

24:45.645 --> 24:47.912
Yeah, you're right.
I guess I would've.

24:47.980 --> 24:49.213
I'm going this way.

24:49.281 --> 24:51.515
That's -- clay,
that's not the right way!

24:51.583 --> 24:53.216
Yeah, I know.
You're the human compass.

24:53.284 --> 24:55.285
You know what? Just do
whatever the hell you want.

24:55.352 --> 24:57.086
I'm going this way.

24:57.154 --> 24:58.754
[ groans ]

25:00.690 --> 25:04.392
* away *

25:04.460 --> 25:07.695
It's amazing how you can enter
the building a functioning adult

25:07.762 --> 25:10.097
And immediately revert to the
geek you were in high school.

25:10.164 --> 25:11.865
I'll tell you a secret.

25:11.932 --> 25:13.433
I was a geek, too.

25:13.501 --> 25:15.501
I wore headgear until the end
of my sophomore year.

25:18.071 --> 25:20.038
There she is.

25:20.106 --> 25:22.674
So, geek, why don't you
take a chance

25:22.741 --> 25:25.443
And ask the popular girl
to dance?

25:25.510 --> 25:27.878
Maybe because
the popular girl

25:27.946 --> 25:29.413
Is already here
with somebody else.

25:29.480 --> 25:31.381
I'm sure it's not
what it looks like.

25:31.448 --> 25:32.848
It's okay.

25:32.916 --> 25:35.551
It wouldn't be the '80s without
a cameo by crocodile dundee.

25:35.618 --> 25:37.753
I just wish he wasn't
on a date with brooke.

25:37.820 --> 25:39.821
Of course
he showed up with alex.

25:39.889 --> 25:41.223
It's a retro dance,
after all.

25:41.290 --> 25:43.324
Why should I expect
anything new?

25:43.392 --> 25:45.126
Alex:
Just go talk to her.

25:45.193 --> 25:48.162
We might be in a high school,
but we're not <i>in</i> high school.

25:48.229 --> 25:49.463
Come on.

25:50.832 --> 25:52.966
Oh, god, they're coming
this way. Come on, let's hide.

25:53.034 --> 25:55.401
Correction -- we're definitely
back in high school.

25:55.469 --> 25:58.203
* don't give yourself away *

25:58.271 --> 26:00.839
* surrender *

26:00.906 --> 26:02.507
[ cheers and applause ]

26:11.352 --> 26:13.786
Just, uh,
grab that flower pot.

26:13.853 --> 26:15.488
Looks like we're gonna have to
break a window.

26:18.493 --> 26:19.760
Ah!

26:19.828 --> 26:20.461
Ah!

26:20.528 --> 26:23.597
[ jamie shouts ]

26:23.664 --> 26:25.131
I'm hit! I'm hit!

26:30.235 --> 26:32.213
Hold up! Hold up!
Hold up! Hold up!

26:32.213 --> 26:33.746
Jamie, wait!

26:33.814 --> 26:34.680
It's us!

26:36.015 --> 26:38.116
Oh. Hey, guys.

26:40.036 --> 26:41.603
Are you gonna
tell my parents?

26:41.671 --> 26:44.305
What, that we were
stupid enough to fall
for your little prank?

26:44.373 --> 26:46.207
Not if you don't.

26:46.275 --> 26:47.308
Okay, deal.

26:47.376 --> 26:48.976
But I need your help.

26:54.048 --> 26:56.517
[ chuckles ] my locker
was down there.

26:56.585 --> 26:57.818
Mine was over here.

26:57.886 --> 27:00.286
Do your remember
how lucas pimped it out

27:00.354 --> 27:02.221
The first day
of senior year?

27:02.289 --> 27:05.024
I wonder if the combination
still works.

27:05.091 --> 27:06.858
Brooke davis.

27:06.926 --> 27:09.194
What?

27:09.261 --> 27:11.095
[ gasps ]

27:11.163 --> 27:13.431
Shut up!
That's so bad!

27:13.498 --> 27:15.065
Oh.

27:15.133 --> 27:18.701
Looks like
she really loves him.

27:18.769 --> 27:20.736
Do you ever think things
were simpler then?

27:20.804 --> 27:21.971
What,
the love triangle

27:22.072 --> 27:23.372
Between you,
lucas, and peyton?

27:23.440 --> 27:25.474
No. No.

27:25.542 --> 27:27.342
Yeah.

27:27.410 --> 27:30.546
I guess
love's never simple.

27:30.614 --> 27:31.914
All right.

27:31.982 --> 27:34.383
What actually happened
with you and julian?

27:34.451 --> 27:37.052
Because I do <i>not</i> understand
why you're not together.

27:37.120 --> 27:38.853
He's here with alex.

27:38.921 --> 27:41.188
So are you.
The boy version.

27:41.255 --> 27:43.222
That's different.

27:43.290 --> 27:45.790
He made it clear that
she's his priority right now,

27:45.858 --> 27:48.325
And I think
he has feelings for her.

27:48.393 --> 27:50.326
Whether or not
he admits that,

27:50.394 --> 27:52.728
I can't be the girl
who's with the guy

27:52.795 --> 27:54.629
Who's in love
with someone else.

27:54.697 --> 27:56.431
Not again.

27:56.499 --> 27:58.632
Kylie:
Tell me about it.

27:58.700 --> 28:01.168
Hey, is there someplace
around here a girl can lie down?

28:02.771 --> 28:04.972
Oh, this -- this'll do.

28:05.040 --> 28:07.243
* ...The avenue,
I never thought I'd meet... *

28:07.311 --> 28:09.178
Are you okay?

28:09.246 --> 28:10.381
Yeah.

28:10.483 --> 28:13.285
I...[sighs]
just need a little break.

28:13.352 --> 28:14.419
* ...Like you *

28:14.487 --> 28:16.554
Who is she?
I don't know.

28:16.622 --> 28:18.790
* with auburn hair
and tawny eyes *

28:18.857 --> 28:21.091
Okay, just, um...

28:21.159 --> 28:23.660
* hypnotize me through *

28:23.728 --> 28:26.396
You...Take care.

28:26.463 --> 28:28.698
[ groans ]

28:28.765 --> 28:31.033
* and I ran... *

28:31.101 --> 28:33.402
Ow!

28:33.470 --> 28:36.438
Ow! Wait!

28:36.506 --> 28:38.006
Ow. [ sighs ]

28:38.074 --> 28:41.909
* I ran all night and day *

28:41.977 --> 28:44.511
[ australian accent ] g'day,
mate. What can I get you?

28:44.579 --> 28:46.013
No, let me guess --
foster's?

28:46.080 --> 28:47.080
[ chuckles ]

28:47.148 --> 28:49.415
Yeah, uh...

28:49.483 --> 28:52.785
Hey, uh, I guess it's weird for
you that I'm here with brooke.

28:52.852 --> 28:55.053
But, you know,
just for the record,

28:55.121 --> 28:56.620
I'm actually a nice guy.

28:56.688 --> 28:57.788
Okay, nice guy.

28:57.856 --> 28:59.790
Well,
also for the record --

28:59.858 --> 29:01.759
If you ever hurt her,

29:01.826 --> 29:04.561
I will hunt you down
across the outback.

29:04.629 --> 29:07.363
And I'm not talking about
the steakhouse.

29:07.431 --> 29:09.598
Although, I will hunt you down
there, as well.

29:09.666 --> 29:12.667
Fair enough.

29:12.734 --> 29:14.468
* aurora borealis comes in... *

29:14.535 --> 29:18.738
Well, uh,
thanks for the beer, mate.

29:20.741 --> 29:24.375
I wouldn't last five minutes
in the outback.

29:24.443 --> 29:27.881
* I ran so far away *

29:27.948 --> 29:30.250
* I just ran *

29:30.317 --> 29:34.386
* I ran all night and day *

29:34.454 --> 29:36.021
* I couldn't get away *

29:37.156 --> 29:39.924
Kylie:
Hey, can you help?

29:39.991 --> 29:43.126
My hair's stuck
in the bloody door.

29:43.194 --> 29:45.795
[ chuckles ]
how did that happen?

29:45.863 --> 29:48.331
Actually,
I don't want to know.

29:48.398 --> 29:49.698
Never mind.
I'll go find someone.

29:49.766 --> 29:51.433
No, don't go.

29:54.303 --> 29:58.005
I'm sorry
I was such a bitch before.

29:59.607 --> 30:01.374
It's okay.

30:04.044 --> 30:06.410
No.

30:06.478 --> 30:08.312
It's not.
[ sighs ]

30:10.882 --> 30:13.350
It -- it's just...

30:13.417 --> 30:15.418
[ sighs ]

30:15.486 --> 30:18.687
Clay told me
that he didn't believe in love.

30:18.755 --> 30:22.957
And then
you come along,

30:23.025 --> 30:25.292
And I realized
what he really meant

30:25.360 --> 30:28.663
Was that he didn't believe
in love with someone like me.

30:28.730 --> 30:31.498
Kylie, there's more to it
than that.

30:31.566 --> 30:33.567
No.

30:33.634 --> 30:36.235
Guys see me as a body,

30:36.303 --> 30:39.037
Someone to shag.

30:39.105 --> 30:40.940
I'm lucky
if they even buy me breakfast.

30:41.008 --> 30:43.842
* I just ran *

30:43.910 --> 30:45.277
Here.

30:45.345 --> 30:47.079
[ grunts ]

30:47.146 --> 30:48.113
Cut it.

30:48.181 --> 30:49.814
What? No way.

30:49.882 --> 30:52.016
Ugh. It's just hair.
It's gonna grow back.

30:52.084 --> 30:53.250
No. You're drunk.

30:53.318 --> 30:55.452
And why do you have scissors
in your purse?

30:55.520 --> 30:58.521
I was gonna
slash your tires.

30:58.589 --> 31:00.456
Oh.

31:00.524 --> 31:02.524
Just cut my hair,
you bitch.

31:02.592 --> 31:05.827
Plus, it will still smell like
strawberries, anyway.

31:15.870 --> 31:18.037
Nathan: I can't believe it.
You were right.

31:18.105 --> 31:19.739
Imagine that.

31:19.806 --> 31:22.174
It might be nice if you
gave me the benefit
every now and then

31:22.242 --> 31:24.276
Instead of just the doubt.

31:24.343 --> 31:26.044
You're right, man.

31:26.112 --> 31:27.745
I was -- I was out of line
back there.

31:27.813 --> 31:29.914
I'm sorry.

31:32.784 --> 31:35.619
Nate, there's something
that I've never told you.

31:35.687 --> 31:38.956
And I don't know why
I've never told you,
but I just didn't.

31:39.024 --> 31:41.925
I used to be married...

31:41.993 --> 31:43.794
Before you and I met.

31:43.862 --> 31:45.462
Her name was sara.

31:45.530 --> 31:46.797
[ scoffs ]

31:46.864 --> 31:48.432
Right.

31:48.499 --> 31:51.969
She leave you after
you started sleeping
with all those women?

31:52.036 --> 31:54.705
No. Actually, she died.

31:57.442 --> 31:59.143
[ greg laswell's "girls just
want to have fun" plays ]

32:02.613 --> 32:06.081
Geez, clay. I...

32:06.149 --> 32:07.315
[ sighs ]

32:07.383 --> 32:08.616
I'm sorry, man.

32:08.683 --> 32:10.584
I thought --
I thought you were joking.

32:12.753 --> 32:15.286
Why didn't
you ever tell me this?

32:15.353 --> 32:18.188
I was your agent.

32:18.256 --> 32:20.389
And then
you became my friend.

32:20.456 --> 32:23.490
Look, I know that I should have
told you a long time ago,

32:23.558 --> 32:26.158
But I'm telling you now

32:26.225 --> 32:29.192
Because I get
how hard it is for you...

32:29.260 --> 32:31.661
Being away from haley
so much.

32:31.729 --> 32:33.562
[ vehicle approaches ]

32:33.630 --> 32:37.866
* ...They wanna have fun *

32:37.934 --> 32:39.968
Whoa, slow, slow, slow!

32:40.035 --> 32:41.369
No, whoa, whoa!

32:41.436 --> 32:44.637
Aah! Don't hurt me!

32:44.705 --> 32:46.305
Ma'am, no, no.
We're not gonna hurt you.

32:46.373 --> 32:47.640
It's just
my friend here --

32:47.708 --> 32:49.642
You see, he's been wandering
through the woods

32:49.710 --> 32:50.943
For the entire day,

32:51.011 --> 32:52.744
And all he wants to do
is get back to tree hill

32:52.812 --> 32:55.713
So he can spend the next
few hours home with his wife

32:55.781 --> 32:58.149
To celebrate her birthday.

32:58.216 --> 33:00.517
You're nathan scott.

33:02.319 --> 33:03.853
You're a basketball fan,
huh?

33:03.920 --> 33:07.456
Well, I do live
in north carolina, honey.

33:07.523 --> 33:09.958
I can take you
back to tree hill.

33:10.025 --> 33:12.493
But I only have room
for one.

33:14.396 --> 33:16.930
Tell haley I said
happy birthday.

33:16.998 --> 33:19.165
There's no way
I'm leaving you out here.
No, it's okay.

33:19.233 --> 33:20.967
I'll catch the next ride.

33:21.035 --> 33:22.835
Clay, come on.
Nate.

33:22.903 --> 33:25.004
Go be home
with your wife.

33:26.739 --> 33:28.740
Go.

33:34.379 --> 33:35.879
Thanks.

33:35.947 --> 33:36.947
* that's all they really want *

33:37.015 --> 33:38.315
[ sighs ]

34:00.519 --> 34:02.955
Please tell me
you didn't kill that nice lady

34:03.022 --> 34:05.993
And dump her body because
there's no way I can spin that.

34:06.061 --> 34:07.295
No,
I just bought her car.

34:08.664 --> 34:10.297
Get in.
Let's go home.

34:10.364 --> 34:12.998
Nice.

34:13.067 --> 34:15.268
[ revs engine ]

34:30.713 --> 34:33.614
* every time I think of you *

34:33.683 --> 34:36.184
* I feel a shock right through
with a bolt of blue *

34:36.252 --> 34:38.753
It's funny.

34:38.820 --> 34:42.022
I always had a thing
for the guys in shop class.

34:42.090 --> 34:44.291
What happened
to your date?

34:44.358 --> 34:46.993
Come on.
We're just friends.

34:47.061 --> 34:49.295
Ah, the irony is palpable.

34:53.032 --> 34:58.169
You know I wasn't trying
to make you jealous, right?

34:58.236 --> 35:00.104
You said
you weren't coming,

35:00.171 --> 35:02.739
So...

35:02.807 --> 35:04.641
Why did you?

35:06.243 --> 35:10.345
It was a misguided attempt
to find some clarity

35:10.413 --> 35:14.181
On the night before the biggest
day of my professional life.

35:14.249 --> 35:16.483
But going back
to high school

35:16.551 --> 35:18.918
Just makes me
feel like a geek.

35:18.986 --> 35:21.320
Not exactly
a confidence booster.

35:24.591 --> 35:27.359
Well, I've seen
my share of '80s movies,

35:27.427 --> 35:29.461
And if I've learned
anything

35:29.528 --> 35:31.863
Is that nothing
boosts the geek's confidence

35:31.930 --> 35:33.564
Like a kiss
from the cheerleader.

35:47.008 --> 35:49.810
I'll see you
at work tomorrow.

35:49.877 --> 35:52.678
You're gonna do great.

36:00.919 --> 36:02.252
Hey, brooke?

36:06.189 --> 36:08.824
This isn't gonna be easy,
is it?

36:08.892 --> 36:11.426
You and I being friends.

36:13.562 --> 36:15.930
No. [ chuckles ]

36:15.997 --> 36:17.664
[ voice breaking ]
but it's better

36:17.732 --> 36:19.532
Than not being in each other's
lives at all.

36:21.468 --> 36:24.736
[ intro to cheap trick's "smile"
plays ]

36:34.480 --> 36:40.717
* my darling little ones,
can you hear me? *

36:40.784 --> 36:46.487
* I'll know in my heart
when you need me *

36:46.555 --> 36:54.961
* I'll always be there
when you want me to-o-o-o *

36:58.065 --> 37:01.300
* take a look around the world *

37:01.368 --> 37:03.101
* it's a wonder *

37:03.169 --> 37:04.336
Hey, there.

37:04.403 --> 37:07.905
I'm alexander.

37:07.973 --> 37:09.841
You have any idea
where our dates are?

37:09.909 --> 37:11.442
Hopefully
somewhere together.

37:11.510 --> 37:13.244
That doesn't bother you?

37:13.311 --> 37:15.412
[ chuckles ]

37:15.480 --> 37:17.881
Some advice,
from one alex to another --

37:17.948 --> 37:20.182
Don't fall in love
with brooke davis.

37:20.250 --> 37:21.917
Those two
are gonna end up together,

37:21.985 --> 37:23.385
Even if
they don't know it yet.

37:23.453 --> 37:25.086
Yeah, okay.

37:25.154 --> 37:27.021
Um, well,
how do you know, then?

37:27.089 --> 37:29.390
Brooke
still loves julian.

37:29.458 --> 37:31.425
And I know because...

37:31.493 --> 37:33.326
So do I.

37:33.394 --> 37:37.596
* well, you know how it feels *

37:37.664 --> 37:40.465
* well, it seems like a dream *

37:40.533 --> 37:46.069
* and I just can't believe
it's real *

37:49.239 --> 37:51.373
* imagine you a*

37:51.441 --> 37:54.309
Well,
whose car is this?

37:54.376 --> 37:56.310
It's yours.

37:59.013 --> 38:01.214
Happy birthday, hales.

38:01.281 --> 38:07.036
* I'll always be there
if you want me to-o-o-o-o *

38:07.103 --> 38:07.937
Oh!
[ squeals ]

38:12.809 --> 38:14.342
* when I look into your... *

38:14.410 --> 38:16.544
It's not that bad.

38:16.612 --> 38:18.012
Bollocks.
It looks bloody awful.

38:18.081 --> 38:19.215
[ chuckles ]

38:19.283 --> 38:21.952
But you have been
a trooper.

38:22.019 --> 38:23.720
So we can go
and have a shag.

38:26.491 --> 38:29.893
I can't believe I'm actually
gonna say this, but, um...

38:29.960 --> 38:31.027
I can't.

38:31.095 --> 38:32.695
I mean, I can, but...

38:32.763 --> 38:34.230
We can't.

38:34.298 --> 38:35.932
Right.

38:36.000 --> 38:39.068
So your flat or mine?

38:39.136 --> 38:40.703
No, I'm serious.

38:40.771 --> 38:43.538
It's not that I don't want to.
Believe me, I do.

38:43.605 --> 38:45.137
It's just...

38:45.205 --> 38:48.805
[ sighs ] my ex-girlfriend,
who is also my roommate.

38:48.873 --> 38:50.139
It's messy.

38:52.109 --> 38:53.842
But we could
go get some pancakes,

38:53.910 --> 38:55.577
Maybe soak up
some of that alcohol.

38:55.645 --> 38:58.212
Your profile was right.

38:58.280 --> 39:00.381
You are a nice guy.

39:00.449 --> 39:03.584
It's good to know
there's still a few out there.

39:03.651 --> 39:06.186
* don't be afraid *

39:06.253 --> 39:07.854
Thank you.

39:10.624 --> 39:12.057
Hey!

39:12.125 --> 39:13.892
[ laughs ]

39:13.959 --> 39:15.560
Are you ready to move on?

39:17.562 --> 39:19.196
Yeah.

39:19.264 --> 39:22.532
* everything will be all right *

39:22.600 --> 39:27.904
* when I see you smile,
my love *

39:27.971 --> 39:33.876
* I just can't hide my love *

39:33.943 --> 39:35.911
* when you call out my name *

39:35.978 --> 39:37.277
Mmm.

39:37.345 --> 39:38.512
I'm sorry
I missed your dance.

39:38.579 --> 39:39.813
It's okay.

39:39.880 --> 39:41.214
Is this where
you went to school, huh?

39:41.281 --> 39:43.082
Yeah.

39:43.150 --> 39:45.250
Show me around?
Okay.

39:45.318 --> 39:49.120
* I just can't believe
it's real *

39:51.090 --> 39:57.361
* imagine you and me
now and ever *

39:57.428 --> 39:58.629
[ chuckles ]

39:58.696 --> 40:00.263
[ gasps ]

40:00.331 --> 40:03.166
Well, I guess junk and fergie
actually did a good job.

40:03.233 --> 40:05.935
Maybe we should bump them up
on the babysitting list.

40:06.003 --> 40:07.269
Let's get him to bed.

40:07.337 --> 40:11.239
* if you want me to *

40:13.509 --> 40:15.744
[ strains ]

40:15.812 --> 40:17.412
* when I look into your eyes *

40:17.480 --> 40:19.614
Happy birthday, mama.

40:19.682 --> 40:21.782
Thank you, baby.

40:21.850 --> 40:26.987
* a wonderful spell
that I'm under *

40:27.054 --> 40:29.889
* we're not just a dream *

40:29.957 --> 40:35.794
* meant for me and you *

40:35.861 --> 40:42.532
* when I see you smile,
my love *

40:42.600 --> 40:44.801
What are you
gonna wish for?

40:44.868 --> 40:48.470
I already have
everything I ever wanted.

40:48.538 --> 40:51.406
* when you call out my name *

40:51.474 --> 40:54.342
* well, you know how it feels *

40:54.410 --> 40:57.478
* well, it seems like a dream *

40:57.545 --> 40:59.079
* and I just can't believe *

40:59.147 --> 41:00.947
So I just want to say
how grateful I am

41:01.015 --> 41:03.149
That you're all
taking this ride with me.

41:03.217 --> 41:06.218
So, let's make
someone's favorite movie.

41:06.286 --> 41:08.519
* take a look around the world *

41:08.587 --> 41:12.122
* it's a wonder *

41:12.190 --> 41:13.323
Okay, places, everyone.

41:15.259 --> 41:16.426
Man: Picture's up.

41:19.230 --> 41:20.664
Roll camera.

41:20.732 --> 41:22.432
We're rolling.

41:23.801 --> 41:25.335
Spinning.

